  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Monster Codex pg. 177</em></p><p><strong>Aura</strong> strong evocation <strong>CL</strong> 12th</p><p><strong>Slot</strong> none; <strong>Price</strong> +1 bonus; <strong>Weight</strong> -</p><p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"modules/pf-content/assets/PathfinderSocietySymbolN.gif\" title=\"Legal only for Ratfolk PCs\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\"><strong>Description</strong></h3>This ability can be placed only on a <em>corrosive </em>or <em>corrosive burst </em>weapon (<em>Pathfinder RPG Ultimate Equipment</em> 138). When the wielder of a <em>catalytic </em>weapon hits a creature, the weapon triggers a devastating chemical reaction that burns the struck creature. The creature struck must succeed at a DC 15 Fortitude save, or take 1d6 points of acid damage at the start of its turn for 1d4 rounds. Successive hits with the <em>catalytic </em>weapon increase the duration but don't add to the damage. The creature can attempt to neutralize the reaction as a full-round action as if it were on fire (including bonuses for dropping and rolling on the ground or jumping into water). Anyone who hits a creature subject to this chemical reaction with a natural weapon or unarmed strike takes 1d6 points of acid damage.</p><p><h3 class=\"framing\"><strong>Construction</strong></h3><strong>Requirements</strong> Craft Magic Arms and Armor, <em>acid arrow</em>; <strong>Price</strong> -</p>",
